#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""seed_hard_v2_b8.py - batch 8 for the N>=100 hard-set lane (target ~80/100).

Same contract as batches 1-7: soundness admission through task_curator gates;
difficulty screening against the served 14B is a later arm. Batch 8 doctrine:
contract density over textbook fame, extended to stateful and search-shaped
contracts. Difficulty comes from precise multi-clause prose contracts
(validation ordering, exact exception types and messages, tie-breaking,
budget semantics, trace shapes) not famous algorithms. Domains in this file
are ones batches 1-7 barely touch: combinatorial ranking and unranking
(permutation rank, Gray-code rank, kth combination), bounded sequence
processes (look-and-say with run overflow, longest digit run, Collatz under a
step budget), BFS and graph contracts (knight moves, grid shortest path,
union-find components, strict bipartite check, one-way portal board,
multi-source spread radius), stateful trace simulations (LRU cache,
min-stack, ring buffer), fold and ledger contracts (k-smallest ranking, bank
ledger with formatted errors, inventory reservation), and strict parsing or
encoding (URL splitting, quoted-printable decoding, INI sections, minimal LCS
diff, Fletcher-16 checksum, markdown outline numbering). Each task is a
single top-level function; the prompt states the full contract in prose with
no solution code; the hidden tests assert exact semantics on adversarial
edges.
"""
